The API client needs it when it have to fill the body of the POST apiProductOrder for an



order 
that 
will 
add 
a 
product 
(subscription). 
It 
has 
to 
put
@type:ApiProducActionAddtDeviceLocationVerification and use this json schema structure
for the body. The future Operate API Product catalog will permit the API Client to know that
for 
this 
specific 
ProductSpecification 
the 
@type 
value 
must 
be
ApiProducActionAddtDeviceLocationVerification 
the 
URL 
of 
the
ApiProductActionAddDeviceLocationOptimisation.schema.json.
