Call flows
In order to better understand how to manage strongly typed shemas, this call flow is an
illustrative way of doing it.
Getting product offering and product specification
Channel Partner
Channel Partner
Operator TMF936
Operator TMF936
Operator Schema Repository
Operator Schema Repository
Channel Partner has already retrieved the ProductOffering of Device Location Verification
TMF936 GET /productSpecification/{id}
retrieve a productSpecification, example for Device Location Verification
TMF931 200 OK
productSpecification in response, example for Device Location Verification:
- allowedAction.@targetProductActionSchemaLocation.@type:https://mycsp.com:8080/tmf-api/schema/Customer/ApiProductActionAddDeviceLocationVerification.schema.json (for action=add)
- allowedAction.@targetProductActionSchemaLocation.@type:https://mycsp.com:8080/tmf-api/schema/Customer/ApiProductActionModifyDeviceLocationVerification.schema.json (for action=modify)
- targetProductSchema.@schemaLocation:https://mycsp.com:8080/tmf-api/schema/Product/ApiProductDeviceLocationVerification.schema.json
GET https://mycsp.com:8080/tmf-api/schema/Customer/ApiProductActionAddDeviceLocationVerification.schema.json
response with the json schema
GET https://mycsp.com:8080/tmf-api/schema/Customer/ApiProductActionModifyDeviceLocationVerification.schema.json
response with the json schema
GET https://mycsp.com:8080/tmf-api/schema/Product/ApiProductDeviceLocationVerification.schema.json
response with the json schema
Posting product order use case
Channel Partner
Channel Partner
Operator TMF931
Operator TMF931
Operator Schema Repository
Operator Schema Repository
Channel Partner already has the schema of ApiProductActionAdd for Device Location Verification (see previous TMF936 Product Catalog call)
TMF931 POST /apiProductOrder
order a product, example for Device Location Verification where ApiProductActionAdd has a specific schema for Device Location Verification:
- productOrderItem.productAction.@type:ApiProductActionAddDeviceLocationVerification
- productOrderItem.productAction.@type:https://mycsp.com:8080/tmf-api/schema/Customer/ApiProductActionAddDeviceLocationVerification.schema.json
we assume Operator already has the schema of ApiProductActionAdd for Device Location Verification
TMF931 201 Created
instanciated productOrder in response, example for Device Location Verification:
- productOrderItem.productAction.@type:ApiProductActionAddDeviceLocationVerification
- productOrderItem.productAction.@type:https://mycsp.com:8080/tmf-api/schema/Customer/ApiProductActionAddDeviceLocationVerification.schema.json

